{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"title_main","type":"text","text":"# AI Logging System — Data Retrieval Flow\n\nLogs are generated from multiple sources. We never send raw logs directly to the model. They pass through a Retrieval Layer → Parser → Filter before the agent ever sees them.\n\nThe reason is simple: during an incident, logs can explode to 100+ per minute. Sending everything fills up the context window, slows response time, and increases cost dramatically.","x":-600,"y":-600,"width":1400,"height":160,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"sources_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-600,"y":-380,"width":1400,"height":180,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"src_elastic","type":"text","text":"### 📋 Elasticsearch\nApplication Logs","x":-580,"y":-360,"width":220,"height":80,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"src_kubernetes","type":"text","text":"### 🐳 Kubernetes\nContainer Logs","x":-320,"y":-360,"width":220,"height":80,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"src_cloudwatch","type":"text","text":"### ☁️ CloudWatch\nSystem Logs","x":-60,"y":-360,"width":220,"height":80,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"src_rds","type":"text","text":"### 🗄️ RDS\nDatabase Logs","x":200,"y":-360,"width":220,"height":80,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"src_s3","type":"text","text":"### 🪣 S3 Bucket\nLoad Balancer Logs","x":460,"y":-360,"width":220,"height":80,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"retrieval_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-600,"y":-120,"width":1400,"height":340,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"retrieval_title","type":"text","text":"## 🔄 Retrieval Layer","x":-580,"y":-105,"width":300,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_step1","type":"text","text":"**Step 1**\nConnect to Log Source\n\nEstablish connection to Elasticsearch, CloudWatch, Kubernetes client, etc.","x":-580,"y":-30,"width":230,"height":120,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_step2","type":"text","text":"**Step 2**\nDefine Time Range\n\nStart narrow — last 5 minutes. Widen only if more context is needed.","x":-320,"y":-30,"width":230,"height":120,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_step3","type":"text","text":"**Step 3**\nFilter by Criteria\n\nSeverity level, service name, keywords. Only relevant logs pass through.","x":-60,"y":-30,"width":230,"height":120,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_step4","type":"text","text":"**Step 4**\nLimit Results\n\nCap at ~50 logs per query. Keeps API costs low and response times fast.","x":200,"y":-30,"width":230,"height":120,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_step5","type":"text","text":"**Step 5**\nExtract & Format\n\nOutput a consistent structure regardless of source — same interface every time.","x":460,"y":-30,"width":230,"height":120,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"ret_interface","type":"text","text":"```\nretrieve_logs(source, time_range, filters)\n```\nThe agent calls this one interface — it does not care whether logs came from Elasticsearch or CloudWatch.","x":-60,"y":120,"width":520,"height":80,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"volume_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-600,"y":280,"width":1400,"height":520,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"volume_title","type":"text","text":"## ⚠️ Volume Problem\n\nDuring incidents, logs can spike from hundreds to **thousands per minute**. You cannot send all of them to the model — it fills the context window, slows analysis, and costs a fortune.","x":-580,"y":300,"width":660,"height":120,"color":"2"},
		{"id":"volume_stat","type":"text","text":"## 100+ logs/min\nduring an active incident\n\nContext window fills up.\nCost spikes.\nModel gets overwhelmed.","x":120,"y":300,"width":280,"height":120,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"vol_solution","type":"text","text":"### Solution — Two-Layer Approach\nFilter first. Summarize if filtering alone is not enough.","x":-580,"y":440,"width":1360,"height":60,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"priority_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-600,"y":520,"width":420,"height":240,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"priority_title","type":"text","text":"### 🔴 Priority-Based Selection","x":-580,"y":530,"width":380,"height":50,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"priority_body","type":"text","text":"FATAL and ERROR logs are always retrieved first.\n\nWARN and INFO are included only if there is room left.\n\nSerious problems are never skipped — even when logs are flooding in.","x":-580,"y":590,"width":380,"height":150,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"dedup_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-140,"y":520,"width":420,"height":240,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"dedup_title","type":"text","text":"### 🔁 Deduplication","x":-120,"y":530,"width":380,"height":50,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"dedup_body","type":"text","text":"If \"Connection timeout\" repeats 100 times — send it **once** with metadata:\n\n- How many times it occurred\n- First & last timestamp\n- Which services were affected\n\nThe model understands the pattern without reading 100 identical lines.","x":-120,"y":590,"width":380,"height":150,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"service_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":320,"y":520,"width":460,"height":240,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"service_title","type":"text","text":"### 🎯 Service-Aware Filtering","x":340,"y":530,"width":420,"height":50,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"service_body","type":"text","text":"Prioritize logs from services that are **actually experiencing issues**.\n\nExample: Payment service at 50% error rate vs Auth service that is healthy → focus on payment logs first.\n\nError rate determines which service gets attention.","x":340,"y":590,"width":420,"height":150,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"summarization_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-600,"y":880,"width":1400,"height":320,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"sum_title","type":"text","text":"## 📝 Progressive Summarization — When Filtering Is Not Enough","x":-580,"y":900,"width":700,"height":60,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"pass1_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":-580,"y":975,"width":620,"height":200,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"pass1_title","type":"text","text":"### Pass 1 — Quick Summarization\n*(Cheap, Fast Model)*","x":-560,"y":990,"width":400,"height":60,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"pass1_body","type":"text","text":"Takes chunks of filtered logs and produces one-line summaries.\n\n```\n[ERROR] DB timeout (47x, 10:15–10:18) - payment-db unreachable\n[WARN]  High memory (3x, 10:16–10:17) - api-gateway at 87%\n[ERROR] API 500s (23x, 10:17–10:19) - downstream failures\n```\n200 raw lines → ~20 structured summaries","x":-560,"y":1050,"width":580,"height":110,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"pass2_bg","type":"text","text":"","x":80,"y":975,"width":680,"height":200,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"pass2_title","type":"text","text":"### Pass 2 — Deep Analysis\n*(Main, Capable Model)*","x":100,"y":990,"width":400,"height":60,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"pass2_body","type":"text","text":"Receives the summaries — not raw logs — and performs root cause analysis.\n\nThe expensive model now works with clean, structured data instead of a raw log dump.\n\nResult: Context limits respected. Costs stay predictable. Quality stays high.","x":100,"y":1050,"width":640,"height":110,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"model_node","type":"text","text":"# 🤖 AI Agent\n\nReceives only what it needs:\n- Prioritized errors\n- Deduplicated entries\n- Service-filtered logs\n- Structured summaries\n\nFull context window available for actual reasoning.","x":-100,"y":1260,"width":400,"height":200,"color":"5"}
	],
